CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 14, 1951, pg. 28, reads: "Show Promise - Young members of the Centre Avenue YMCA swimming team which finished second in a swim meet at the Downtown YMCA last week are pictured above.  The youngsters, who show promise of future swimming great, are, left to right, Sige Burdon, first-place winner in the 40-yard free style and second-place winner in the 100-year free style; Alvin Abrams, Victor Hill, who finished second in diving; John Brown and Billy Getting.  Norman Johnston, coach, and David Getting, mascot, are shown in the second row. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Sige Burdon, Alvin Abrams, Victor Hill, John Brown, and Billy Getting preparing to dive, with David Getting and coach Norman Johnston in back, in Centre Avenue YMCA indoor swimming pool
